Example 8: Methylammonium (MA) substitution in CsPbI3 perovskite
=================================================================

Physical system
---------------
The cubic alpha-phase CsPbI3 (Pm-3m, a=6.3225 A) is a lead-iodide
perovskite where Cs occupies the A-site. Replacing some Cs with
methylammonium (MA = CH3NH3+) gives the mixed MA_x Cs_{1-x} PbI3
solid solution, relevant for hybrid perovskite solar cells.

This example uses a 4x4x4 supercell (320 atoms: 64 Cs, 64 Pb, 192 I)
and substitutes 2 of the 64 Cs sites with MA molecules (x=0.03125),
enumerating all inequivalent configurations under Pm-3m symmetry.
Output is LAMMPS data files (conf.data) for classical force-field
calculations.

The MA molecule is read from MA.xyz (8 atoms: C, N, 6H). SOD places
it with the centre of mass at the Cs site and a random orientation
(Shoemake uniform quaternion sampling).

Files
-----
  INSOD                SOD input (FILER=2, LAMMPS)
  SGO                  Symmetry operations for Pm-3m (space group 221)
  supercell.cif        4x4x4 CsPbI3 supercell in P1 (320 atoms)
  MA.xyz               Methylammonium geometry (DFT-PBE optimised, Angstrom)
  template_in.lammps   LAMMPS input template with # sod_type_map entries

How to run
----------
1. Run combsod:   ../../bin/combsod
2. Run genersod:  ../../bin/genersod
3. LAMMPS data files appear in n02/cXX/conf.data

Replace pair_coeff and charge values in template_in.lammps with your
chosen force field before running LAMMPS. Bond and angle terms within
the MA molecule are not written by SOD and must be added separately.

Expected output
---------------
9 inequivalent configurations out of C(64,2) = 2016 total arrangements.

Each conf.data will contain 334 atoms:
  62 Cs + 64 Pb + 192 I + 2 C + 2 N + 12 H
(replacing 2 Cs sites with 2 MA molecules of 8 atoms each).
MA orientations are random and differ between genersod runs.
